    <title>DIGISOL Launches 1MP CMOS Plastic Bullet AHD Camera</title>
    <link>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10562/digisol-launches-1mp-cmos-plastic-bullet-ahd-camera.html</link>
    <description>Digisol has recently announced the launch of DG-CM3230P, the 1MP CMOS Plastic bullet AHD Camera that comes with a 3.6 mm fixed lens and IR cut filter. DG-CM3230P comes with both cost-effectiveness of analog cameras and also the superior video quality of HD resolution.
The camera sports 30 powerful IR LED to give a clear view in absolute darkness. With the IR LED turned on, you can easily see up to 20m to 30m distance.</description>
    <pubDate>Fri ,13 May 2016 12:06:09 +0000</pubDate>
    <name>Team TechTree</name>
    <nid>10562  at http://www.techtree.com </nid>

  <item>
    <title>Kia Motors America Launches Apple CarPlay With UVO</title>
    <link>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10560/kia-motors-america-launches-apple-carplay-uvo.html</link>
    <description>Adding to the constant evolution in telematics and infotainment, Kia Motors America (KMA) today announced that the 2017 Sportage and 2016 Optima, when equipped with a compatible navigation system or UVO3, will be offered with Apple CarPlay compatibility when the vehicles arrive at Kia retailers during the second quarter.
Additionally, customers who have previously purchased the 2017 Sportage or 2016 Optima equipped with a compatible navigation system or UVO3 will be provided with a downloadable update via myuvo.com that will be available beginning in the third quarter.</description>
    <pubDate>Fri ,13 May 2016 10:07:31 +0000</pubDate>
    <name>Team TechTree</name>
    <nid>10560  at http://www.techtree.com </nid>
    <comments>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10560/kia-motors-america-launches-apple-carplay-uvo.html#comments</comments>
  </item>
  <item>
    <title>Uber-like App For Live Streaming</title>
    <link>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10559/uber-app-live-streaming.html</link>
    <description>WorldRelay, an Austin-based new media company is announcing 121Live, an app that facilitates paid peer-to-peer live video by connecting subscribers looking for a new experiences with GPS-equipped streamers who have Smartphones, GoPros, 360° panoramic cameras, or drones.
"121Live is an app where anyone with a smartphone can become a streamer, creating custom video from their point of view. At the same time, 121Live subscribers will get to decide exactly what they want to see from the app on their smartphone or TV," explained WorldRelay co-founder, Ellis Hill.</description>
    <pubDate>Fri ,13 May 2016 09:59:12 +0000</pubDate>
    <name>Team TechTree</name>
    <nid>10559  at http://www.techtree.com </nid>
    <comments>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10559/uber-app-live-streaming.html#comments</comments>
  </item>
  <item>
    <title>Zebronics Unveils Multifunction Speaker Zebstaion 2</title>
    <link>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10558/zebronics-unveils-multifunction-speaker-zebstaion-2.html</link>
    <description>Zebronics, India’s leading supplier of IT peripherals, consumer electronics  and surveillance products has updated its award winning range of speakers with their new model Zebstaion 2.
Zebstation 2 speaker has a built-in clock and dual alarms. The alarms can be snoozed for up to 10 minutes. These functions work even when the speaker is in switched off mode. The speaker sports a 1200mAH battery and the battery can be charged using a bundled adapter. It also comes with sleep feature which can used to automatically switch off the speaker at pre-configured time.</description>
    <pubDate>Fri ,13 May 2016 09:54:05 +0000</pubDate>
    <name>Team TechTree</name>
    <nid>10558  at http://www.techtree.com </nid>
    <comments>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10558/zebronics-unveils-multifunction-speaker-zebstaion-2.html#comments</comments>
  </item>
  <item>
    <title>L’oreal  Collaborates With Tech Start Up Founder Factory</title>
    <link>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10557/l-oreal-collaborates-tech-start-founder-factory.html</link>
    <description>L’Oréal has  announced its investment in the Founders Factory, a leading global multi sector digital accelerator and incubator, co-founded by Brent Hoberman, Henry Lane Fox and Jim Meyerle, based in London. L’Oréal is Founders Factory’s exclusive partner for investments in Beauty tech startups worldwide. This will allow L’Oréal to deeply connect itself to a global ecosystem of world-class startups and entrepreneurs operating in the field of beauty, in line with L’Oréal’s CEO Jean-Paul Agon vision of the transformative power of digital for beauty.</description>
    <pubDate>Fri ,13 May 2016 09:46:50 +0000</pubDate>
    <name>Team TechTree</name>
    <nid>10557  at http://www.techtree.com </nid>
    <comments>http://www.techtree.com/content/news/10557/l-oreal-collaborates-tech-start-founder-factory.html#comments</comments>
  </item>
